These programs assumes that the input file is document-term matrix, 
which is created by the ../wikipedia2matrix. 
* shrink_mat: remove the rows or columns that have limited number of non-zeros
  i.e. remove too rare word, or too short document
* tfidf: calculate tfidf
* show_matrix: show the contents of the matrix using word for debugging purpose
* normalize_row: normalize the length of the row vector for k-means, etc.

